      • buySharesOfStock

        public void buySharesOfStock(java.util.Date date,
                             double amount,
                             java.lang.String stockSymbol,
                             java.lang.String portfolioName)
                      throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        For a given valid date verified by ITradingInformation.isTradingHours(Date), it buys share for the company provided in stockSymbol at a given amount under a given portfolio. If any of these entries are incorrect, it throws IllegalArgumentException otherwise returns true.
        Specified by:
        buySharesOfStock in interface StockInvestmentStrategies
        Parameters:
        date - for which user needs to buy stock in Date.
        amount - in double which describes total cost of investment of user for this purchase.
        stockSymbol - unique company ticker symbol in String to identify stock of that company.
        portfolioName - name of the Portfolio in String for which user wants to buy stock.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - in case parameters provided are incorrect.
